column1: Title: Teen Birth Rate per 1,000 Population Ages 15-19 | KFF
Data are by place of residence. Population includes females 15-19 years old.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), [National Vital Statistics Reports (NVSR), Vol. 66, No. 1: Births: Final Data for 2015](https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/nvsr/nvsr66/nvsr66_01.pdf), January 5, 2017.
1. US teen birth rate excludes data from the territories.
